culminating in a powerful vision of “the abyss of the deity.” Here, Vioulac articulates a portrait of Christianity as a religion of mourning, waiting for a god who has already passed by, a form of ever-present eschatology whose end has always already taken place. With a preface by Jean-Luc Marion, Apocalypse of Truth presents a major contemporary French thinker to English-speaking audiences for the first time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHeidegger, Martin,-1889-1976. 0aLogos (Philosophy) 0aLogos (Philosophy). 0aOntology. 0aTruth. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  amartin heidegger, philosophy, philosopher, philosophical, crisis, translated works, translation, truth, disclosure, apocalypse, mystery, finitude, karl marx, giorgio agamben, alain badiou, slavoj zizek, ontology, logos, christianity, christians, religion, religious studies, mourning, eschatology, destiny, equalization, god, deity, teleology, cyberspace, machination.1 aMarion, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarion, Jean-Luc.1 aPeterson, Matthew J.1 aPeterson, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021 Englishz978311075415508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021z9783110753929oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226766874423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226766874/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 202